I am grateful to be one of the recipients of the ATAP community service awards. I was chosen to receive the Hope and Inspiration award for my work with #GirlYes within the community and nationally. 

All Things Are Possible Foundation (ATAP) serves Burlington County, New Jersey, families with academic enrichment programs with a differentiated and highly valuable offering: life-changing, developmental programs with emphasis on academics, athletics, awareness, and arts.

ATAP serves 400 children annually with out-of-school-time (OST) programs, including before and after school care, full-day fall, spring, and summer programs, STEAM workshops, and other academic and cultural enrichment programs for K-8 and teens. 

Moments like this remind me that I am living in answered prayers and that God Is Faithful. At times you can loose sight of the bigger picture when your tired and frustrated however, everything works together for those who love him and are called to his purpose. #ChimereNicole #mrsusa  #girlyes
Have to be careful where I step, my daughters need to see the path I leave them.

The PHIRST and The Phinest.
It was never IF, but ALWAYS when 🩷💚. December 17, 2023 marks a monumental milestone in my life. 

I’m finally excited to tell the world, I Phinally got my 20 pearls! I am apart of the illustrious sisterhood of Alpha Kappa Alpha sorority, Incorporated. 

It may start with me but it will never end with me, let’s continue to build the legacy of Phiner woman. This is #GirlYes exemplified. And since this is “Serious Business” I will make sure the path my daughters walk is clear! So if you needed the reminder, It is NEVER too late, you have all of the tools as your disposal to be successful, and NOW is the time to accomplish them all.
